Iranian students are willing to die for their country's nuclear program.
They formed a human shield.
Several hundred university students formed human shields around nuclear facilities in Iran.
With their gesture they want to express their support for their country's nuclear program in the face of a possible Israeli attack.
The students began praying Tuesday at noon outside the facility and then chanted death slogans to the U.S. and Israel.
Several hundred university students formed human shields around the uranium-based nuclear technology center in the Iranian city of Isfahan on Tuesday.
They intend to show that they are willing to defend their country's nuclear program with their own lives.
The International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA), in a recent report, found that Iran, according to all indications, is striving to obtain nuclear weapons.
In Israel there is talk of a possible attack on Iranian nuclear facilities.
The students began to pray at noon outside the Isfahan nuclear facility and then hurled death slogans against the U.S. and Israel.
