Daily menu of an obese child: no breakfast and dinner sausages
More than a third of children aged between 9 and 13 years have problems of overweight, where overweight affects 9% of the school population and obesity 5%.
Obese children mostly come from families with an unhealthy lifestyle, according to current research.
It is again demonstrated what is the importance of the environment where it grows for a healthy development of the person, as well as the models that serve as a reference.
At the table, obese children eat, for example, sausages at least twice as often as children from normal-weight families.
For dinner, more than 19% of obese people had eaten chips the day before the analysis, which is linked to the prevention program "Obesity is not a coincidence."
In families of overweight children there is no habit of practicing sports, which is applicable to most families today, where only 15% of children responded that their parents, at least once a week, find time for physical exercise.
Survey of 900 children
The survey was conducted at the end of the last school year and involved almost 900 basic education children from all over the Czech Republic.
It was already the second edition of the "Obesity is not a coincidence" program, which is supported by the General Health Insurance Company and the Unilever company.
So far, more than 12 thousand children have participated in the project from the 4th to the 8th grade.
An adequate diet and plenty of exercise as a family are determining factors, which significantly reduce the number of overweight and even obese children.
"Only half of the children surveyed have answered that they have five meals a day according to the regime: breakfast, lunch, lunch, snack and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet," reads one of the results of the survey.
No breakfast but with cold meat for dinner
Specialists warn that, in a healthy development, the details are also important, which also count, such as having a fixed time for breakfast with the family.
In the Czech Republic, however, only 23% of schoolchildren's families eat breakfast at the same time.
In most families, everyone eats breakfast alone.
But the worst thing was to discover that in 10% of households nothing is breakfast.
Breakfast is, however, the basis of a correct daily diet.
The study shows that in families of obese children, unhealthy French fries are consumed much more frequently.
Almost everyone - regardless of weight - drinks sweet soft drinks daily (70%).
As a general rule, more than 40% of the children surveyed play sports, however, among their parents this result is reduced to less than half, only 15%.
Prepare your diet
The next phase of the study made it possible for the chosen kids (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to create their own diets from all possible offers according to their tastes and opinions.
"The food preferences of Czech children aged 12 to 15, from the point of view of healthy eating, are far from ideal."
Among her favorite foods are pasta, meat and sweets
"The popularity of sweet soft drinks is especially alarming," warns the final report of the study.
As the main meal, the pasta takes the cake and is closely followed by poultry.
Practically, children always reject the legume and the taste for fish and vegetables is very low.
Switching to healthy habits
At the same time, the study shows that children are willing to change their eating habits if they receive the right information.
"In the control group of the participants in the study, who filled out the questionnaire after finishing the prevention program "Obesity is not a coincidence", there was in many cases an important change in favor of the principles of a healthy diet," says the results of the study.
It is striking, for example, what is related to sweet drinks, where many children would begin to prefer normal and running water.
Children would also choose poultry and fish for the main meal more frequently in the questionnaire and restrict the consumption of sweet food and flour derivatives.
The stylist must also be a good psychologist, say the professionals
In the introductory article, How Stylists Learn, I already complained a bit that the initial lessons were already quite loaded.
I had no idea how that would go.
Lectures by three professionals in the field, how to dress problematic characters and, in addition, a seminar on how it works in the world of entertainment.
And it will be worse.
The closer the final exams are, the more information and practical tasks await us
And although the course takes place every Saturday and Sunday, there is no longer room for a pin.
We have studied with the director, Alena, (in the course there is no man) on how to dress the woman who does not have perfect symmetry.
And so is the vast majority.
Someone is short-necked, someone has a stylized figure without the right curves and someone is overweight.
The stylist must know how to optically soften wide shoulders, lengthen a neck or recreate the necessary curves
We have been given certain tricks on how to make the body stand out for women of the type of Jennifer Lopez, with huge breasts and hips but narrow waist and at the same time not dress it in a too challenging way.
If, for example, the difference between the waist and hips is so much that the skirt or pants do not fit, it is worth having at least an extra piece of fabric sewn to measure.
They certainly won't regret it, because the clothes you feel perfectly are priceless.
With a custom skirt you will feel much better than with one that does not stop moving, getting up, dancing at the waist, etc.
Stylized body can be allowed to wear clothes with pleats, ornaments, embroidery or draping.
There are certainly many kinds of diverse information and bodies, so I'm glad I have the whole week to put all this information in order in my head.
And even so, I'm afraid that with the assigned task, I already have more than enough.
Each participant in the course has been assigned two celebrities, to whom he must design two costumes: one for the day and one for the night.
You have to take into account the current appearance, the fashion style that suits the person in question.
I have had to "dress" Miranda Kerr, maybe you know her from the Victoria's Secret campaign.
I scream inside, for me it is much better than, for example, Britney Spears or Christina Aguilera, who lately will have gained a hundred kilos (please take into account the exaggeration), or the very young Selena Gómez.
The dresses have to be cut out of magazines or searched on the internet and printed, and then graphically elaborated.
The moodboard, which is what the complete result is called, also expresses our personal style and our relationship with graphic design.
It is also important to think about the graphic part of the styling.
The stylist, therefore, does not only dress physically, but also deals, for example, with the product pages in magazines (of specific topics, such as trends, bags, coats, etc.).
The stylist and designer Mario Kameník told us about all this.
But all this is already for Sunday.
The stylist must have a global vision.
The three specialist guests animated Saturday's conference with information on all types of bodies.
Stylist Honza Pokorný, fashion designer Jakub Polanka and fashion photographer Ben Renč.
Jakub reminded us that fashion is an illusion and the stylist should know how to take advantage of this.
And a good stylist knows how to work with the same garment in different ways.
Variability is, in this case, fundamental.
Thus, the so-called trench coat (or as they say in English, trench-coat) can be dressed in the classic with jeans and t-shirt, but also serves to dress the naked body with heels and photograph it as if it were actually a dress.
Or just roll up your sleeves and raise your neck to get a totally different image.
"Play with it," he insisted.
What I value most is the following advice: "To start working, you need to know all the rules first."
"Then you can break them," Jakub said.
Finally it is clear to me why we memorize all these formulas, what is combined with what, why, if it turns out that in fashion magazines we find different results.
Not to mention the parades.
Thanks to photographer Ben, I know that a stylist has to have more types of clothes in the reserve than they intend to photograph.
Thus, for a fashion story that has ten pages (therefore, ten outfits), you have to have prepared, ready to use, at least fifteen.
And also that the photos the clothes work in combination with other garments, all of them different from those used in reality.
All this must be taken into account when designing the outfit.
Honza Pokorný assured us that image and style alone are, in many cases, half of the success.
Just look at Madonna, who is not exactly an extraordinary singer, but the image and marketing have made her a world star.
In the Czech Republic, at the moment, there is still no clear trend to use the services of stylists.
Even famous people also find it useless (my skills are enough, my physical appearance is not so important).
And when someone asks us for our services, we must bear in mind that it is very likely that they indicate a size very different from their real (smaller).
Then it remains only to guglear and find out if the magazines of the heart have already written on the subject, if a certain celebrity has gained weight / slimmed, etc.
On Sunday, Honza and Mario insisted that the stylist is not enough to orient himself in fashion, but that he has to understand the outfit.
During your work, you should especially communicate with the people you dress, so it is essential to be a good psychologist.
He knows how to value people, he does not miss it, he defends their opinions.
"When a director hires you to sort out the costumes and complete it with nice clothes, you can't take and throw away everything there was and say, 'Wow what a horror.'"
"Find at least a couple of things that you can ponder and recommend so that someone can wear them," says Mario.
He himself also showed us that everything must fit in the so-called "placovka", that is, the job board.
This is fixed around the waist and all the necessary tools are there.
They are objects such as scissors, like scissors, removers, or safety pins. There is also nylon thread (which serves the stylist during the photo shoot of products such as bags or hats), special clips for attaching garments in front, if this is larger (pins and other types of hooks are not allowed, as they could damage the fabric), or a sewing set.
In order not to stay in passive listening and put something into practice, we have learned to coat the soles of our shoes.
Even during photo shoots in the studio, on a flat surface, you could damage the sole and even more the outside.
And we did nothing but clothe and coat.
We couldn't touch the shoes with the scissors so as not to damage them by accident.
So you had to be very skilled.
Mario has given me a joy by praising my work without reservation.
The truth is that I am not very good at those skills.
This is only a small part of everything we have heard throughout the weekend, in the second part of the course.
I've already realized that dedicating myself to styling on a professional level is not a rosy path, but I don't care exactly what people say.
Need for Speed: The Run competes all over America.
Review
A trip, initially carefree, is complicated by a series of oversights unbecoming of a routine trip during the morning shift.
To some extent expectations were met, but that is useless if, in fact, nothing extraordinary was intended.
The new installment, to which The Run is added to the title, aroused great expectations even before its premiere.
It promised that it would give new airs to the old racing saga Need for Speed and, as a result of what was shown, it appears as a game that should not end up being an action genre again.
We are also curious to know what the inserted scenes would look like, where the main character gets out of the car and walks on his own foot.
As often happens in NFS series, the results do not vary much from what we expected.
There are races that can be considered acceptable, but in the total calculation points are lost because of absurd failures, which have already been appearing in the series for years.
In reality, they cannot even be called errors, but rather the incomprehensible reluctance of programmers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are introduced to a story, whose protagonist, Jack, has certain personal problems; to solve them, he is offered to participate in an illegal race throughout America.
You sit behind the wheel on the West Coast, in San Francisco, and your mission is to get the first to New York.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then more than fifty races.
It follows that each race takes place along a different route and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite diverse and interesting.
That way, one doesn't even remotely get the feeling that the game always offers the same thing.
Some of the environments are even pleasing to the eye, although the technical level of the graphic is equivalent to that of previous installments of the series.
Therefore, it is nothing to write home about.
But the walk through the desert, the autumn landscape or the high snow-capped mountains produce a very pleasant visual effect.
In addition, careers are diversified from time to time by an atypical element.
So, for example, in the desert you find a sandstorm that decreases visibility.
On the other hand, in the mountains you have to be careful not to be buried by an avalanche.
According to that, each of the races is very well developed.
There are only a couple of models, but that's enough.
For a moment, you try to overtake a required number of rivals (normal in a classic race), then you try to gain time (classic timed duel) and then a duel awaits you against a single opponent.
In the midst of all this, sometimes the police appear, which only makes things even more difficult.
The novelty is the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape from someone and you have to help him, always pressing the button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are far fewer landscapes in the game than you would expect (in particular there are only three).
But the final result is positive, because this element does not become annoying and, in the context already mentioned, is one of the elements that make the game more interesting.
The driving model follows in the footsteps of previous episodes.
That means that today it is no longer a big deal, but it cannot be said that it is bad.
If you're looking for a realistic simulation, you can look elsewhere.
But a race conceived with enough action suits this style of driving, although we can find something better among the games of the competition.
So far, so good.
But problems arise after a certain time.
Unlike the correctness of driving models, collisions are no longer the case.
Games of this type can not be expected to recreate deformations and complicated collisions, but in fact before a hit against any object, you can not predict how your car will react, so not everything is in order.
It is typical that, when making a very tight overtaking or driving the car with normal traffic, there are only slight frictions, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up doing uncontrolled pirouettes.
Or it even ends up totally destroyed.
Thanks to the reset system, no big problems arise, but it can put you in a bad mood.
The resets are programmed in such a way that, when you suffer an accident or leave the track, the game returns you to the last rescue point on the track.
However, in each race there are only five resets available.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it is nothing more than a help in case something does not go well, but it is not very reliable.
Sometimes, even the reset does not help, it only helps to learn the given stage by heart.
A big disadvantage of the game is that the same events are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, you have to enter in a specific way; otherwise, they are impossible to take.
Other times you find "civilian" vehicles somewhere always with the same configuration, even if you are the first, fifth or arrive five minutes before or after.
This makes rage especially in situations, when you see that two cars that go to the meeting in opposite directions, your opponent overtakes without problems, but when you arrive, you must turn or brake.
It is the same when you arrive, because it is programmed because the "surprise" will always happen right under your nose.
Adversaries also have one more advantage.
Throughout the game you will reach places where, regardless of the moment, you will always be overtaken by the same opponent in the same place.
In addition, this happens at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must arrive before you, at any price.
When it goes in front of you, it makes it difficult for you to see the cars coming from the front, so at first you can make porridge of the car.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspense and adrenaline, but the execution is so apparent that you will surely be disappointed immediately.
And it's a shame, because although the model of the trip is simple, the game is fun and actionable, so it is often not possible to follow in detail what happens or where.
And it really doesn't matter, if the merit takes the idea with fifty exclusive tracks or the classification in the race so that there is no room for boredom, or anything else.
An unusual idea is the change of cars during races.
You have to be attentive to the gas pumps on the side of the road, because right there you have to change cars, although in the vast majority of cases what you have will suffice.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are suitable for urban areas, American strong cars for straight highways and exotic supercars for technical driving, for example on curvy mountain roads.
In addition to the main narrative thread, a parallel challenge thread also appears, that is, there are races in specific places that you will know from the stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also experience points for your profile, which serves both challenges and stories.
When reaching the upper level, the driver opens up several possibilities, starting with the car and ending with funds for the profile.
At the same time, an online Autolog function is connected, which compares your results with those of other players and makes other community functions available.
One of the hardest elements to understand is how the last race in history is made.
With the car you reach the metro tunnel (pass), where you start running in the dark on the tracks (pass).
The speedometer marks you between 150 and 200 km / h (pass) and, suddenly, from behind you the subway convoy arrives and takes you ahead without further ado.
In the newsroom we will surely have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the programming of the game no one thought even a little or if the authors really take us for a bunch of fools.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the general visual effects are in most cases pleasant, sometimes even superb.
Well, what a pity that, in the most tense moments, the image quality is reduced and, sometimes, in a serious way.
This especially affects accidents where many participants are involved, when the continuous image quality is no longer valid.
The audio is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In order to please most of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the category "each of his father and mother", but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game just for its music.
The final feeling of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore quite confusing.
If the game avoided absolutely silly mistakes, we would have trouble claiming that The Run is the best NFS game of recent years.
It gives the feeling that the game is not finished.
Fun is guaranteed, but be prepared because mistakes will hit you in the eyes with the force of airport reflectors.
The choirs of the Carolina University will participate in the concert "Velvet Students".
The joint celebration of International Student Day and the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution as a musical experience will take place for the third time at the Festa Academica festival.
During it, twenty choirs from secondary and university centers will be presented.
The festival revolves around two concerts on November 17.
"Carolina University has a high participation in the festival."
Among the current choirs are the choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and the Faculty of Humanities, on the festival committee is the rector Václav Hampl," said the head of the organization, Jakub Čaloun.
The summit of the whole festival is free admission for all audiences to the concert of the high school choirs, which will be held on March 17 at 2 pm in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The program features Czech jazz musician Karel Růžička and his Celebration Jazz Mass.
In the evening, the concert "Velvet Students" will be held at the venues of the Municipal House in Vynohrady, in which university choirs will participate, including the choir of the Carolina University.
The purpose of the Festa Academica is not only to celebrate International Students' Day with dignity and remember the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present choral music to the public at the highest level and encourage collaborative creation among young people.
The main organizer is the Czech Choral Union in collaboration with the Jan Kepler Secondary School.
All events were supported by the Mayor of Prague, Bohuslav Svoboda, and the Rector of Charles University, Václav Hampl.
The Festival will take place between November 16 and 20 between Prague and Pardubice.
The calendar offers, in addition to celebratory concerts, a whole series of musical events, impromptu student shows and morning concerts.
Those interested can find more information on the festival page www.festaacademica.cz
