Meder, the pool collector discovers the outstanding specimens in her research in Hungary.
Next to the magnificent medicinal baths such as the 100-year-old Széchenyi bath in Budapest, there are the waters with nitrates in a unique karst cavity (cavity baths in Miskolc-Tapolca), as well as thermal baths, whose pools are alkaline waters and are located in a bottle-shaped building (Városi Termálfürdö in Jászberény).
