This was the work of the caleño who identified the body of Alfonso Cano
A lofoscopist from Cali went down in history as the man who confirmed the death of "Alfonso Cano".
The work of these officials is key.
On November 4, a lofoscopist of the CTI of Cali went down in history as the man who confirmed the identity of the FARC's top leader, "Alfonso Cano," through the comparison of his fingerprints.
Of the seven lofoscopists who work in the CTI section, that week it was the turn of Eliazar González, a man from Puerto Tejada who has been working in the area of judicial investigation for 21 years.
At the beginning of his career, González worked in municipalities of Chocó, where he often had to go for more than five days in the jungle to reach the place where the bodies that had to be identified were.
In 2000 he moved to the capital of the Valley and, after completing the corresponding courses, he specialized in lofoscopy, which is the study of frictional skin, that is, the palms of the hands and feet.
The week of the operation against alias Alfonso Cano, Eliazar was warned to wear clothes for at least three days.
Something big was waiting for him.
On Friday night he left for Cauca in a helicopter from Palmira.
He knew that he had to identify two corpses and that one of them was suspected to be the man who led the oldest guerrilla group in the world, so they asked him to carry the decadactylar card of Guillermo León Sáenz (his real name).
However, when he arrived with the investigation team at the site where the body was located, he did not recognize it because of his physical appearance, as it was very different from what he had seen in the media.
He was beardedless, dressed like a local peasant, without glasses and much thinner.
But footprints don't lie.
Accompanied by a Galtonian magnifying glass, ink, a transplanter and a flashlight, Eliazar compared the fingerprints of the corpse with those of the card.
His eye did not fail him: it was "Alfonso Cano".
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was in charge of confirming to Defense Minister Juan Carlos Pinzon that he was indeed the top leader of the FARC.
In search of the footprint
For a fingerprintist of the Sijin of Cali, the recognition made by President Juan Manuel Santos to Eliazar González, in the press conference for the operation against "Cano", is very significant.
Many people do not know our work.
Dactyloscopy is an exact science, with no margin for error, which can be key in solving crimes.
Apart from the identification of corpses, lofoscopists support investigations for crimes such as theft and homicide and confirm the identity of those captured.
When caught, many criminals present false ID cards or do not have papers.
We fingerprint them and look them up in the database.
The investigator said that, in a case of theft, he had to remove a piece of wall from a house, because in that place the thief had supported his hand to take out a safe full of jewelry and money.
"The walls are difficult because they are not appropriate surfaces to get a fingerprint, but in that case we were able to obtain the fingerprint of the whole hand and identify the offender, who had participated in different thefts," he recalled.
Fingerprints can also rule out or reaffirm suspects in homicide cases.
They recently found a dead man, with bottles of liquor around him.
Through the investigation it was determined that a relative could be suspected of the crime and, indeed, a footprint on the bottle matched.
Although this does not guarantee that he was the murderer, it does place him at the scene of the crime.
A CTI dactyloscopist explained that on objects "fingerprints are taken with chemical or physical reagents."
When they appear, a transplanter or tape is used to lift them.
After this, the prints are sent to the Asif, which is the criminal database, or to the Registry.
"The problem is that there are still many undocumented Colombians," said the CTI expert.
He clarified that not everything is as shown on the CSI TV show.
Just as not everything that glitters is gold, not everything that is touched becomes a footprint.
However, if it can be used, if the respective comparison is made.
